data.title: Coffee County, AL
data.text:
NOTICE OF COFFEE COUNTY COMMISSION REVISED SUBDIVISION REGULATIONS

By Resolution of the Coffee County Commission, adopted on the 27th day of June, 2022, and pursuant to the powers and jurisdiction granted by Code of Alabama 1975, 11-24-1 et seq., the Coffee County Commission updated the Subdivision Regulations for Coffee County, Alabama.

The updated regulations shall be in force and applicable to the development of all subdivisions in the unincorporated areas of Coffee County from and after the 1st day of January, 2023.

Below are links to the newly adopted regulations and a summary of the major changes. Printed copies may be purchased at the Coffee County Engineer’s Office located at 1165 East McKinnon Street, New Brockton, Alabama. Please contact the County Engineer’s Office at 334-894-6112 with questions.
